content.description: TR short face on right side of wall
TR wall just right of Who gives a dam?
content.location: just right of Who gives a dam

content.description: Same chossy start as Dammed if you do. Then tend right passing a PITA tree. Climb a steep section and then head up and right to a 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: Same as Dammed if you do

content.description: This route shares the 1st few bolts with Dammed with you don't. A chossy start to bolt #3. tend left following more bolts and better rock to the top.
content.location: The center route (roughly) that shares its start with Dammed if you don't

content.description: Start just right of Damit! Janet! under a steep section to an alcove and first high bolt. Clip second bolt with 60 cm sling. Clip 3rd bolt (Roof) and move under said bolt. Make hard Heel Hook/Mantle move passing just barely to the climber's left of the bolt line. Clip and follow remaining bolts up and right to anchors, being careful to stay away from chossy corner to the right.
content.protection: 10 or so bolts and 2 bolt anchor.
content.location: just right of Dam it! Janet!

content.description: Climb the bore hole chute on left side of face. Exiting right at end of said bore hole and wander up to the right surmounting a small roof to the top.
content.location: The bore hole chute on left side of face

content.description: Start directly under high 1st bolt. Balance up onto "nose" at chest height. Walk up slab and clip the 1st bolt using a 60 cm sling. Heel hook/mantle over the lip and climb up and right on easy terrain. Pull small roof and then again up and right to a third roof.  Skirt this roof on right side or don't and then climb up and slightly right to anchor 10' right of "Dam the Torpedoes"' anchors.
content.location: Just right of Dam the Torpedoes

content.description: This route climbs the wandering slab just left of Dammed if you do. Be careful, chossy bits abound.
content.protection: 10 or so bolts and a 2 bolt anchor
content.location: 10' left of Dammed if you do

content.description: Area above Safe Harbor Dam Breast. It is approximately 5.25 miles from the north parking, a quarter mile before the bridge
